         pool to allocate the DivIDE/ZXATASP/ZXCF memory.
20110207 peripherals/disk/disk.c: fix more transposed arguments in memset calls
         (thanks, Stuart Brady) (Fred).
20110207 peripherals/nic/enc28j60.c: add missing #include <string.h> (Fred).
20110207 machines/machines_periph.c: enable SpecDrum for TC2048 as is has
         a Spectrum compatible edge connector and ROM (Fred).
20110207 machines/machines_periph.c,periph.[ch],peripherals/{ay.c,disk/{beta.c,
         plusd.c},fuller.c,ide/{divide.c,simpleide.c,zxatasp.c,zxcf.c},if1.c,
         joystick.c,kempmouse.[ch],melodik.c,printer.c,scld.c,speccyboot.c,
         specdrum.c,ula.c},periph.h: periph_t does not represent a peripheral,
         but just one port from a peripheral, so rename appropriately.
20110208 machines/spec16.c,memory.h,peripherals/disk/plusd.c: use memory pool to
         allocate the Spectrum 16K uninstalled memory and +D memory (Fred).
20110208 machines/machines_periph.c,periph.[ch],peripherals/{ay.c,disk/{beta.c,
         opus.c,plusd.c},fuller.c,ide/{divide.c,simpleide.c,zxatasp.c,zxcf.c},
         if1.c,if2.c,joystick.c,kempmouse.c,melodik.c,printer.c,scld.c,
         speccyboot.c,specdrum.c,ula.c}: wrap peripheral data up into a type
         and further renames to better match what types represent.
20110209 periph.[ch],peripherals/{disk/plusd.c,ide/{divide.c,zxatasp.c,zxcf.c}}:
         add new "peripheral activated" function and use it to allocate memory.
20110209 ui/{fb/fbjoystick.c,svga/svgajoystick.c}: fix compilation (fixes bug
         #3175619) (rkd77).
20110210 ui/{win32/{debugger.c,win32joystick.c,win32ui.c},xlib/xdisplay.c}:
         more compilation fixes (fixes bug #3176005) (Sergio Baldov).
20110210 periph.[ch]: remove warning about accessing uninitialised value (Fred).
20110213 machine.c,memory.[ch]: reset ROM source to SYSTEM on machine reset
         so tape traps work on machines with fewer ROMs than a machine with a
         custom ROM that is used first (fixes bug #3179123) (thanks, Phil
         Reynolds) (Fred).
20110214 configure.in,ui/win32/fuse.manifest.in,windres.rc: enable win32 themes
         (patch #3179878) (Sergio Baldov).
20110216 machines/{tc2048.c,tc2068.[ch],ts2068.c}: use memory pool for Timex
         fake memory bank, leave memory marked as no bank so that it doesn't
         get marked as writable by the writeable ROM option (Fred).
20110216 ignore fuse.dSYM file (Fred).
20110220 man/fuse.1,ui/win32/{win32ui.c,win32internals.h,win32display.c,
         statusbar.c}: updated Win32 UI code to resemble GTK+ UI;
           - Allow scalers to set window size from menu
           - Restore scaler after restart
           - Resize window when machine selection switches between Timex and
             non-Timex modes
           - Status bar can be hidden completely from menu and command line
           - Status bar icons appear in the same order as GTK+ UI
           - Fix status bar flickering on +2A, +3 and +3e machines due to high
             refresh rate of disk status
           - Properly sized status bar icons part on startup
         (patch #3169039) (Sergio Baldov).
20110319 windres.rc,ui/win32/{Makefile.am,about.[c|h|rc],debugger.c,debugger.rc,
         hyperlinks.[ch],options-resource.pl,win32internals.h,
         win32joystick.[c|rc],win32ui.c}: more Win32 UI code improvements;
         Dialogs:
          - Increase height and spacing of combobox in dialogs due to Visual
            Styles in Vista/7.
          - Standardised buttons width in autogenerated dialogs.
          - Added an About dialog, similar to GTK UI
          - In joystick options, increased the height of joystick types frame to
            accommodate Fuller
          - Identified a bug with joystick buttons higher than four.
         Debugger:
          - Visual styles in Vista/7 increase rows height in ListView controls.
            Adjusted lists and dialog size to allocate 20 rows without scrolling
            (stack).
          - Disassembly list shows 20 rows in Vista/7, however shows 24 rows in
            2000/XP to use full height.
          - Fix partially visible T-states.
          - Fix scrolling in disassembly list (1 LINEUP/LINEDOWN), don't
            mismatch next OP if the top OP was 2 bytes.
          - Enabled ESC key to close the dialog.
         (patch #3201532) (Sergio Baldov).
