         of the AMD AM29F010 flash (modified from patch #3313062) (Guesser
         and Phil).
20110608 peripherals/spectranet.c: beginnings of Spectranet snapshot support.
20110610 peripherals/if1.c: mirror Interface 1 ROM to seconds 8Kb of ROM as in
         the real interface (fixes bug #3314682) (thanks, mcleod_ideafix and
         zx81) (Fred).
20110610 peripherals/spectranet.c: pretty much working Spectranet snapshot
         support.
20110610 peripherals/spectranet.c: remember to restore Spectranet disabled
         state when restoring from snapshot (thanks, Guesser).
20110611 peripherals/spectranet.[ch],z80/{coretest.c,z80_ops.c}: implement
         Spectranet programmable trap support.
20110611 peripherals/spectranet.c: implement the shadow screen bit when reading
         from port 0x033b.
20110611 peripherals/nic/w5100.c: very slightly less stubby W5100
         implementation.
20110611 peripherals/spectranet.c: remember to set paged state in snapshot!
20110613 peripherals/flash/am29f010.c: ensure flash locations > 64Kb can be
         written to.
20110613 memory.c,peripherals/{nic/w5100.c,spectranet.[ch]}: even less stubby
         W5100 emulation.
20110615 peripherals/nic/w5100.c: Spectranet can now make a DNS query!
20110616 peripherals/nic/w5100.c: stop potential deadlock when freeing W5100.
20110616 peripherals/nic/w5100.c: ensure we don't read more bytes than are free
         in our rx buffer.
20110617 peripherals/nic/{Makefile.am,w5100.c,w5100_internals.h,
         w5100_socket.c}: split W5100 socket code out into a separate file.
20110617 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: don't process closed sockets (thanks,
         Winston).
20110617 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: detecting fd
         changes around the select() call could miss the case of a socket being
         closed and re-opened with the same fd, so move to explicit
         invalidation instead.
20110617 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: socket->old_rx_rd is updated by RECV
         command, not by new data becoming available. It should be initialised,
         though.
20110617 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: don't read from sockets that have no
         buffer space left to put the data into.
20110618 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure data is read into the correct
         space in the case of multiple reads.
20110618 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure that socket->fd is initialised
         so we don't try and close() uninitialised values (thanks, valgrind).
20110619 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure that socket->ok_for_io is
         initialised (thanks, Winston and valgrind).
20110619 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure that Spectranet-side sockets
         are properly cleared out on reset.
20110619 peripherals/spectranet.c: implement "deny downstream A15" lack of
         support.
20110619 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: bind sockets when
         we first attempt to use them rather than we the PORT register is
         written to to prevent multiple bind attempts. Also deals with the
         problem of the bytes of PORT being written to in different orders in
         different bits of the Spectranet code.
20110620 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure all sockaddr_in structures are
         zeroed before use.
20110620 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: implement TCP
         client mode.
20110621 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: don't add the UDP header to TCP
         data.
20110621 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: multiple datagrams
         should not be combined in one sendto() call (thanks, Guesser and Chris
         Cowley).
20110621 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: ensure that UDP datagrams which wrap
         around the transmit buffer are not split into two.
20110621 peripherals/spectranet.c: don't try and load Spectranet data from a
         snapshot which doesn't contain it (thanks, Winston).
20110622 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: remember to implement RECV for TCP
         sockets (thanks, Guesser).
20110622 peripherals/spectranet.[ch],z80/{z80.c,z80_ops.c}: implement
         Spectranet "paged via IO port" flag (thanks, Winston).
20110623 peripherals/{spectranet.c,nic/w5100.[ch]}: store core W5100 state in
         snapshots.
20110623 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: add string.h for memset prototype and
         add some more verbose error logging and bind information to help with
         debugging (Fred).
20110626 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: don't double release the lock if a
         bind() call fails (thanks, Sergio Baldov).
20110628 peripherals/{spectranet.c,nic/w5100.[ch]}: reset the W5100 when the
         Spectranet is reset.
20110628 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: don't need to set the sockaddr when
         reading from a socket.
20110630 peripherals/nic/w5100.c: check the return code from select(). Also
         catch the case when a socket is closed between being added to the
         set and the select call, when select will fail with EBADF (thanks,
         Winston).
20110630 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: abort connection if the bind call
         fails.
20110630 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: remove duplicated code when opening a
         new socket.
20110630 peripherals/nic/w5100_socket.c: set SO_REUSEADDR on new sockets.
20110630 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: handle EOF on TCP
         sockets.
20110703 peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: handle TCP server
         mode.
20110703 fuse.c,peripherals/{nic/w5100.c,spectranet.[ch]}: clean up Spectranet
         on exit (Sergio Baldov).
20110703 compat.h,compat/{unix/Makefile.am,socket.c},win32/{Makefile.am,
         socket.c},configure.in,peripherals/nic/{w5100_internals.h,
         w5100_socket.c}: first bits of Win32 compatability layer
         (Sergio Baldov/Phil)
20110708 peripherals/nic/{w5100.c,w5100_internals.h,w5100_socket.c}: ensure we
         don't acquire a lock recursively, thus avoiding deadlock (thanks,
         Winston).
20110724 fuse.c: fix a memory leak while making guesses as to what to do with
         non-option arguments (patch #3376243) (thanks, valgrind) (Sergio
         Baldov).
20110726 ui/gtk/gtkui.c: allow the drag and drop of files from KDE
         (Dolphin/Konqueror) (patch #3376811) (thanks, Diondeville) (Sergio
         Baldov).
20110726 machines/Makefile.am,ui/widget/Makefile.am: fix these issues;
         machines/machines_periph.h is not packed in the tarball,
         ui/widget/options_internals.h is not removed with distclean, and
         ui/widget/options.h no longer exists (patch #3388283) (Sergio Baldov).
