         pause emulation while browsing memory (part of patch #3487118)
         (Sergio).
20120214 ui/win32/{memorybrowser.c,memorybrowser.rc,win32internals.h}:
         more Win32 UI code improvements;
           - Remember memory position when closing.
           - Pause emulation while browsing because it is a modal dialog.
           - Set focus on list when opening.
           - Allow cursor/page keys to scroll.
           - If the scrollbar position is on the bottom, clicking on the down
               arrow didn't show address 0x0000.
           - Allow mouse wheel to scroll when the list has the focus.
           - Use delta displacement of mouse wheel for scrolling.
           - Reduce flickering when scrolling on Windows XP (or later).
           - Fix compile warnings.
         (rest of patch #3487118) (Sergio).
